# Project structure

Use **App Router** under `src/app` (or `app/` at root if the repo already chose no `src`—stay consistent).

## Suggested layout

```
src/
  app/
    (marketing)/          # landing, legal, cookie consent
    (store)/              # catalog, product/[slug], cart, checkout
    admin/                # SPEC: protected /admin/**
    owner/                # SPEC: protected /owner/**
    api/                  # Route Handlers: Stripe webhooks, etc.
  components/
    ui/                   # shadcn primitives (generated)
    ...                   # feature components by domain
  lib/
    supabase/             # server, browser, middleware clients
    stripe.ts             # server-only Stripe helpers
    resend.ts             # server-only email helpers
    utils.ts
  types/                  # shared TS types (or colocate with features)
```

## Rules

- **Colocate** route-specific components under the route folder when they are not reused.
- **Shared domain logic** (pricing, cart rules, role checks) lives in `lib/` or small modules imported by Server Actions—**not** duplicated across pages.
- **Webhooks** live under `app/api/.../route.ts` (or `src/app/api/...`) with **raw body** handling where Stripe requires it.
- **Supabase migrations / SQL** in `supabase/migrations` if using Supabase CLI; keep RLS policies versioned with schema changes.

## Auth and staff routes

- Mirror **SPEC.md** §2.4: middleware or layout guards on **`/admin`**, **`/owner`**; re-check role in every mutating Server Action and sensitive Route Handler.
